# MCP Sentinel — session continuity

## At the start of every session

1. Read `mcp-sentinel/CONTINUATION.md` first (source of truth for status and roadmap).
2. If touching scanners or fixtures, skim `mcp-sentinel/fixtures/CHECK_MATRIX.md`.
3. If touching replay or agent fixtures, skim `mcp-sentinel/fixtures/REPLAY_MATRIX.md`.
4. If touching mutation, skim `mcp-sentinel/fixtures/MUTATION_MATRIX.md`.
5. If touching decoy/AICON, skim `mcp-sentinel/fixtures/DECOY_MATRIX.md`.
6. If touching twin/fleet intel, skim `mcp-sentinel/fixtures/TWIN_MATRIX.md`.
7. If touching live probe, skim `mcp-sentinel/fixtures/live/README.md`.
8. All five phases are **done**. Live MCP probe is **done**. Do not restart Phase 1–5 from scratch unless the user asks for a rewrite.
9. Next work is **optional polish** (remote SSE probe, replay/mutate/decoy/twin UI tabs) — not a new phase unless the user scopes one.

